raw_data.title: Senior Accountant
raw_data.description: Experience should include at least four (4) years in general financial management, and three (3) years of specialized experience in accounting, financial reporting, and financial assessments. This individual will also have five (5) or more years of progressively responsible experience in performing and participating in client engagements, demonstrated ability to lead and direct a staff in performing on financial management projects.

raw_data.title: Project Manager
raw_data.description: The minimum level of experience required for this position includes being a senior-level professional with twelve (12) years federal experience in a technical or managerial business in relation to functional responsibilities.

raw_data.title: Senior Auditor
raw_data.description: Experience should include at least four (4) years in performing various audits and attestation functions and three (3) years of specialized experience in financial audits, operational audits, and agreed upon procedures. This individual will also have two (2) years or more years of progressively responsible experience in performing and participating in client engagements, demonstrated ability to provide guidance and direction for specific projects and increasing responsibility in audit planning, evidence gathering, and providing guidance to staff auditors.

raw_data.title: Senior Business Analyst
raw_data.description: This position requires more than 8 years of progressively more responsible experience in performing and participating in financial management services engagements, including 4 years’ experience with governments, a demonstrated ability to provide guidance and direction for specific projects or subtasks, and increasing responsibility in the design, implementation, and management of financial management projects. Senior analysts’ interface with the client daily and support the completion of project-specific tasks within estimated time frames and budget constraints. They also support presentations, training, and client meetings.

raw_data.title: Senior Data Analyst
raw_data.description: The data management specialist will have a bachelor’s or advanced degree in an appropriate technical field, with at least five years’ direct experience in database methodologies, programming, and system design, and experience in relational database design and programming. Experience in the contemporaneous development of documentation.

raw_data.title: Senior Financial System Analyst
raw_data.description: The senior financial system analyst has 6 or more years’ experience analyzing accounting data and systems developing client solutions with a team, including experience with off-the-shelf accounting system software, and including 2 years of supervisory experience. The senior financial systems analyst prepares documentation, reports, and other deliverables for client approval.
raw_data.key_words: Analyzing Accounting Data,Financial System Analysis,Preparation of Documentation,Reporting

raw_data.title: Financial Systems Analyst
raw_data.description: The financial system analyst has 3 years’ experience analyzing accounting data and systems and developing client solutions with a team, including experience with off-the-shelf accounting system software. The financial systems analyst prepares documentation, reports, and other deliverables for client approval, under the direction of a senior financial system analyst.
raw_data.key_words: Accounting Data,Financial System Analysis,Preparation of Documentation,Reporting
